abstract: I have tried to spend time regularly with the people working on A.I. I don’t know that I can convey just how weird that culture is.
snippet: I have tried to spend time regularly with the people working on A.I. I don’t know that I can convey just how weird that culture is.
lead_paragraph: In 2018, Sundar Pichai, the chief executive of Google — and not one of the tech executives known for overstatement — said, “A.I. is probably the most important thing humanity has ever worked on. I think of it as something more profound than electricity or fire.”

abstract: If you can’t do your job better than A.I., maybe you need another job.
snippet: If you can’t do your job better than A.I., maybe you need another job.
lead_paragraph: A mountain man buys his first chain saw. He comes back to the store a week later complaining that it cuts down only two trees a day when he was told it would cut down 20. The service person says, “Well, let’s see what the trouble is,” and starts it up. The mountain man jumps back and asks, “What’s that noise?” (He’d been sawing without the engine on.)

abstract: The inquiry aims to hold to account Syrian officials considered key architects of a brutal system of detention and torture that has flourished under President Bashar al-Assad.
snippet: The inquiry aims to hold to account Syrian officials considered key architects of a brutal system of detention and torture that has flourished under President Bashar al-Assad.
lead_paragraph: For months, guards at a Syrian prison brutally tortured an American aid worker and threatened to kill her loved ones. She eventually caved to their demands, confessing to crimes she did not commit. A trial that lasted no more than a few minutes followed, and she was ordered executed in late 2016.
